-- Bank of Canada Buys C$990 Million of Securities for One Day
-- B y   I l a n   K o l e t
-- 2011-12-20T19:36:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/bank-of-canada-buys-c-990-million-of-securities-for-one-day-1-.html
The Bank of  Canada  bought C$990
million ($961 million) of securities for one day in multiple
transactions today.  The central bank announced the purchases, aimed to keep
overnight lending rates close to its current target of 1
percent, on its website from Ottawa. Earlier, it said it had
bought C$620 million of securities through special purchase and
resale agreements.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilan Kolet in Ottawa at 
 ikolet@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  